##What does one screen change when people take classes online?

Wechat, chinanewsweekly

Function introduction, here is "China News weekly" the head of the weekly gentleman, the influence has the influence you. Come with me to break through the fog, to find the truth, to watch the Times.

Why is online education hot again?

"By 2020, teachers and students will not have to go to school, but will be able to attend classes at home. ". This is the 2000 Dream Cup Essay contest in the first prize excerpt of a sentence, did not expect in 20 years later today but because of the impact of the new pneumonia epidemic has become a reality.

In recent years, online education has been expected by all circles of society, and it is also a long-lasting topic in the field of education. For the first time since the outbreak, online education has gone from an "option" to a "just-in-time" , to a broader acceptance.

The wave of online learning is surging

More than 100 million primary and middle school students across the country took online classes at home on Feb. 10 in response to a call by the Ministry of Education to "suspend classes without suspension" during the outbreak. This is the development of China's Internet 20 years, the first time the daily teaching of students from offline to the online situation.

In the past week, 31 provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions across the country have postponed their scheduled start times. Many online educational institutions have launched free or low-cost courses across the country, and offline educational institutions and schools have moved classrooms online.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
According to incomplete statistics, up to now, there are more than 20 online education companies offering free courses to students all over the country, such as New Oriental Online, Xueersi online school, ape counseling, homework help, Netease Youdao, and who to learn from.

"In less than 10 days since the launch of the free course, 20 million primary and secondary school students have signed up for the course, which is an accumulation of users for an online education platform that often takes years to complete, " said a person in charge of the platform.

Previously, according to AI media consulting forecast, the number of Chinese online education users will reach 296 million by 2020. During the outbreak of the online education products users focused on trying to speed up the expansion of the size of online education users. There's a whole wave of online learning going on.

Behind the national online learning

Suddenly teaching online is a challenge for teachers used to teaching offline: not only do they have to rewrite lesson plans and make powerpoint presentations, but they also have to learn how to interact with live streaming platforms. Chen Ning, a math teacher at a high school in Shanxi Province, recalled his first online class recently. He described it as "as difficult as re-employment. ".

Weibo online class "roll-over scene" is also everywhere: Biology teacher class was broadcast platform closed, political teacher class forgot to open the wheat... in addition, the Internet class fluency is low, poor experience has also been people's frequent complaints.

These "rollover scene" in let people laugh and cry, but also once again triggered people on the value of online education industry discussion.

"I had been used to teaching offline, but I didn't know what an online course was because I hadn't done it. ". Chen Ning is still busy preparing the courseware, but in just two days of the pilot class, he has been trying to sum up experience, has quickly become familiar with the online teaching process. "although it is a challenge, online education must be the trend of the times, " Chen said.

In fact, after years of development, online education has already developed a relatively mature operating model. With the application and trial of online 1-to-1, small class, double-teacher system and other models, some online education institutions are beginning to take shape on a large scale, has a stable community of learning users.

For example, in order to ensure the learning effect, the Simian Guidance has adopted the unique double-teacher Guidance Pattern, the main teacher teaches the class, the head teacher follows up the child's study. The teacher-in-charge will observe the students'learning status in class, respond to the students'questions through real-time interaction, guide them to attend the class in time, and fill in the gaps after class.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Also like grab the wheat this characteristic function setting, lets each student all have the opportunity through the video on the wheat way, with the lecturer teacher real-time Communication. This is similar to the offline classroom when students are called on to answer questions. It is convenient for teachers to test the effect of learning, but also helps students to improve their interest in learning. Is on the third grade of the primary school lan character more introverted, once on the wheat, was the teacher point to, "feel particularly excited, learning hobbies on the rise, each class are carefully prepared. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Miao Miao, 11, likes ape-assisted video editing and playback. "sometimes if you want to take notes, you can cut them out and copy them slowly. If you encounter a knowledge point that you don't understand very well, you can also watch the playback. " Students can be stimulated to concentrate by dragging and dragging on the screen and completing classroom quizzes online. Online education has long been criticized for its low sense of participation, lack of interaction and lack of interest, which has been largely compensated for and improved.

In this new learning style, students also really feel the "teaching and learning" brought happiness. On February 3rd, ape tutoring began online, with 5 million people studying online the same day. "Really Miss Learning" , there are many students issued such a feeling, which is the real significance and value of online education.

To embrace the future in evolution

In a world where online education is so popular, the challenge remains. At present, the sudden surge in demand, the first test is the stability of the platform, in addition, the teacher force, course content requirements have also increased dramatically.

"online teachers and technicians are working around the clock, " said the head of the online education department of the Simian Counseling Service. Since the outbreak of the disease, the company has offered Free live-streaming classes for students to support their learning, there's a lot invested in this.

It is understood that the free live ape tutorial class mobilized 356 lecturers, 412 assistant teachers, 151 technicians and more relevant staff to continue the "battle. ". For many teachers, the free-to-air lesson is both a defense and a challenge for the education industry.

On the other hand, as a product with high temperature, online education can break the limitation of teacher-student ratio and space-time by means of superior technology and resources. Like Yu Qiuyu, Zhou Guoping, Liu Yong, Zhan Qingyun, Xiong Hao and other famous scholars and young role models that students would not normally meet, they were invited to share their gains through online education platforms, for the benefit of students in more districts. During the epidemic period, ape counseling specially invited Professor Liu Jia of Beijing Normal University to share how to deal with the tension during the epidemic, so that students can conduct effective psychological counseling during this special period.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In response, Yu Qiuyu once commented that, "We don't have to do the same work in every classroom. Students have access to the most cutting-edge knowledge and the best teachers in the world through the Internet, which is a convenience brought to us by modern technology. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
With the support of science and technology, some future "teaching and learning" scenarios are gradually staged in real life: Intelligent tools capture real-time teaching feedback, teachers have more reference basis for lesson preparation; Students don't have to wait for the teacher to save them when they encounter a problem they don't understand. They can scan their mobile phones for instructions on how to solve the problem, teachers have more time for educational innovation..

Simian tutorship and the company's Simian Search, Simian Question Bank, Simian oral math, zebra AI class and other online education products, according to their functional attributes play different advantages, we provide users with a variety of intelligent education services, such as online courses, intelligent exercises and problem analysis, and finally form a systematic, efficient and complete learning loop.

2013 is widely regarded as the first year of online education. Over the past seven years, from Germination to growth, to the outbreak during the hot admission, we have seen online education brought about changes and values, the industry's maturity and improvement needs the tolerance and support of the whole society.

One day the epidemic will pass, and one day the homecoming will come. However, online education will not stop the change of traditional teaching and learning, and its important change and far-reaching influence on the field of education and teaching is probably just beginning.
